90 void COutput::SetSurfaceCSV_Flow(CConfig *config, CGeometry *geometry,
91  CSolver *FlowSolver, unsigned long iExtIter,
92  unsigned short val_iZone) {
93 
94  unsigned short iMarker;
95  unsigned long iPoint, iVertex, Global_Index;
96  su2double PressCoeff = 0.0, SkinFrictionCoeff[3];
97  su2double xCoord = 0.0, yCoord = 0.0, zCoord = 0.0, Mach, Pressure;
98  char cstr[200];
99 
100  unsigned short solver = config->GetKind_Solver();
101  unsigned short nDim = geometry->GetnDim();
102 
103 #ifndef HAVE_MPI
104 
105  unsigned short iDim;
106  su2double HeatFlux;
107  char buffer [50];
108  ofstream SurfFlow_file;
109 
110  /*--- Write file name with extension if unsteady ---*/
111  strcpy (cstr, config->GetSurfFlowCoeff_FileName().c_str());
112 
113  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == TIME_SPECTRAL) {
114  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 10) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
115  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 10) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
116  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 100) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
117  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 1000) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
118  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
119 
120  } else if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() && config->GetWrt_Unsteady()) {
121  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 0) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 10)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
122  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 10) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
123  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 100) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
124  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 1000) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
125  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
126  }
127  else
128  SPRINTF (buffer, ".csv");
129 
130  strcat (cstr, buffer);
131  SurfFlow_file.precision(15);
132  SurfFlow_file.open(cstr, ios::out);
133 
134  SurfFlow_file << "\"Global_Index\", \"x_coord\", \"y_coord\", ";
135  if (nDim == 3) SurfFlow_file << "\"z_coord\", ";
136  SurfFlow_file << "\"Pressure\", \"Pressure_Coefficient\", ";
137 
138  switch (solver) {
139  case EULER : SurfFlow_file << "\"Mach_Number\"" << "\n"; break;
140  case NAVIER_STOKES: case RANS:
141  if (nDim == 2) SurfFlow_file << "\"Skin_Friction_Coefficient_X\", \"Skin_Friction_Coefficient_Y\", \"h\"" << "\n";
142  if (nDim == 3) SurfFlow_file << "\"Skin_Friction_Coefficient_X\", \"Skin_Friction_Coefficient_Y\", \"Skin_Friction_Coefficient_Z\", \"Heat_Flux\"" << "\n";
143  break;
144  }
145 
146  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
147  if (config->GetMarker_All_Plotting(iMarker) == YES) {
148  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
149  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
150  Global_Index = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
151  xCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(0);
152  yCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(1);
153  if (nDim == 3) zCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(2);
154 
155  /*--- The output should be in inches ---*/
156 
157  if (config->GetSystemMeasurements() == US) {
158  xCoord *= 12.0; yCoord *= 12.0;
159  if (nDim == 3) zCoord *= 12.0;
160  }
161 
162  Pressure = FlowSolver->node[iPoint]->GetPressure();
163  PressCoeff = FlowSolver->GetCPressure(iMarker, iVertex);
164  SurfFlow_file << scientific << Global_Index << ", " << xCoord << ", " << yCoord << ", ";
165  if (nDim == 3) SurfFlow_file << scientific << zCoord << ", ";
166  SurfFlow_file << scientific << Pressure << ", " << PressCoeff << ", ";
167  switch (solver) {
168  case EULER :
169  Mach = sqrt(FlowSolver->node[iPoint]->GetVelocity2()) / FlowSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSoundSpeed();
170  SurfFlow_file << scientific << Mach << "\n";
171  break;
172  case RANS:
173 
174  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++)
175  SkinFrictionCoeff[iDim] = FlowSolver->GetCSkinFriction(iMarker, iVertex, iDim);
176  HeatFlux = FlowSolver->GetHeatFlux(iMarker, iVertex);
177 
178  if (nDim == 2) SurfFlow_file << scientific << SkinFrictionCoeff[0] << ", " << SkinFrictionCoeff[1] << ", " << HeatFlux << "\n";
179  if (nDim == 3) SurfFlow_file << scientific << SkinFrictionCoeff[0] << ", " << SkinFrictionCoeff[1] << ", " << SkinFrictionCoeff[2] << ", " << HeatFlux << "\n";
180 
181  break;
182  }
183  }
184  }
185  }
186 
187  SurfFlow_file.close();
188 
189 #else
190 
191  int rank, iProcessor, nProcessor;
192  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
193  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &nProcessor);
194 
195  unsigned long Buffer_Send_nVertex[1], *Buffer_Recv_nVertex = NULL;
196  unsigned long nVertex_Surface = 0, nLocalVertex_Surface = 0;
197  unsigned long MaxLocalVertex_Surface = 0;
198 
199  /*--- Find the max number of surface vertices among all
200  partitions and set up buffers. The master node will handle the
201  writing of the CSV file after gathering all of the data. ---*/
202 
203  nLocalVertex_Surface = 0;
204  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++)
205  if (config->GetMarker_All_Plotting(iMarker) == YES)
206  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->GetnVertex(iMarker); iVertex++) {
207  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
208  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) nLocalVertex_Surface++;
209  }
210 
211  /*--- Communicate the number of local vertices on each partition
212  to the master node ---*/
213 
214  Buffer_Send_nVertex[0] = nLocalVertex_Surface;
215  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) Buffer_Recv_nVertex = new unsigned long [nProcessor];
216 
217  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nLocalVertex_Surface, &MaxLocalVertex_Surface, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_MAX, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
218  SU2_MPI::Gather(&Buffer_Send_nVertex, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Recv_nVertex, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
219 
220  /*--- Send and Recv buffers ---*/
221 
222  su2double *Buffer_Send_Coord_x = new su2double [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
223  su2double *Buffer_Recv_Coord_x = NULL;
224 
225  su2double *Buffer_Send_Coord_y = new su2double [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
226  su2double *Buffer_Recv_Coord_y = NULL;
227 
228  su2double *Buffer_Send_Coord_z = new su2double [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
229  su2double *Buffer_Recv_Coord_z = NULL;
230 
231  su2double *Buffer_Send_Press = new su2double [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
232  su2double *Buffer_Recv_Press = NULL;
233 
234  su2double *Buffer_Send_CPress = new su2double [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
235  su2double *Buffer_Recv_CPress = NULL;
236 
237  su2double *Buffer_Send_Mach = new su2double [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
238  su2double *Buffer_Recv_Mach = NULL;
239 
240  su2double *Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_x = new su2double [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
241  su2double *Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_x = NULL;
242 
243  su2double *Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_y = new su2double [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
244  su2double *Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_y = NULL;
245 
246  su2double *Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_z = new su2double [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
247  su2double *Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_z = NULL;
248 
249  su2double *Buffer_Send_HeatTransfer = new su2double [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
250  su2double *Buffer_Recv_HeatTransfer = NULL;
251 
252  unsigned long *Buffer_Send_GlobalIndex = new unsigned long [MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
253  unsigned long *Buffer_Recv_GlobalIndex = NULL;
254 
255  /*--- Prepare the receive buffers on the master node only. ---*/
256 
257  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
258  Buffer_Recv_Coord_x = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
259  Buffer_Recv_Coord_y = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
260  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Recv_Coord_z = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
261  Buffer_Recv_Press = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
262  Buffer_Recv_CPress = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
263  Buffer_Recv_Mach = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
264  Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_x = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
265  Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_y = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
266  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_z = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
267  Buffer_Recv_HeatTransfer = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
268  Buffer_Recv_GlobalIndex = new unsigned long [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
269  }
270 
271  /*--- Loop over all vertices in this partition and load the
272  data of the specified type into the buffer to be sent to
273  the master node. ---*/
274 
275  nVertex_Surface = 0;
276  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++)
277  if (config->GetMarker_All_Plotting(iMarker) == YES)
278  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->GetnVertex(iMarker); iVertex++) {
279  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
280  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
281  Buffer_Send_Press[nVertex_Surface] = FlowSolver->node[iPoint]->GetPressure();
282  Buffer_Send_CPress[nVertex_Surface] = FlowSolver->GetCPressure(iMarker, iVertex);
283  Buffer_Send_Coord_x[nVertex_Surface] = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(0);
284  Buffer_Send_Coord_y[nVertex_Surface] = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(1);
285  if (nDim == 3) { Buffer_Send_Coord_z[nVertex_Surface] = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(2); }
286 
287  /*--- If US system, the output should be in inches ---*/
288 
289  if (config->GetSystemMeasurements() == US) {
290  Buffer_Send_Coord_x[nVertex_Surface] *= 12.0;
291  Buffer_Send_Coord_y[nVertex_Surface] *= 12.0;
292  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Send_Coord_z[nVertex_Surface] *= 12.0;
293  }
294 
295  Buffer_Send_GlobalIndex[nVertex_Surface] = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
296 
297  if (solver == EULER)
298  Buffer_Send_Mach[nVertex_Surface] = sqrt(FlowSolver->node[iPoint]->GetVelocity2()) / FlowSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSoundSpeed();
299  if ((solver == NAVIER_STOKES) || (solver == RANS)) {
300  Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_x[nVertex_Surface] = FlowSolver->GetCSkinFriction(iMarker, iVertex, 0);
301  Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_y[nVertex_Surface] = FlowSolver->GetCSkinFriction(iMarker, iVertex, 1);
302  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_z[nVertex_Surface] = FlowSolver->GetCSkinFriction(iMarker, iVertex, 2);
303  }
304  nVertex_Surface++;
305  }
306  }
307 
308  /*--- Send the information to the master node ---*/
309 
310  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Coord_x, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_Coord_x, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
311  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Coord_y, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_Coord_y, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
312  if (nDim == 3) SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Coord_z, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_Coord_z, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
313  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Press, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_Press, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
314  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_CPress, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_CPress, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
315  if (solver == EULER) SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Mach, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_Mach, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
316  if ((solver == NAVIER_STOKES) || (solver == RANS)) {
317  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_x, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_x, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
318  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_y, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_y, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
319  if (nDim == 3) SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_z, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_z, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
320  }
321  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_GlobalIndex, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Recv_GlobalIndex, MaxLocalVertex_Surface, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
322 
323  /*--- The master node unpacks the data and writes the surface CSV file ---*/
324 
325  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
326 
327  /*--- Write file name with extension if unsteady ---*/
328  char buffer[50];
329  string filename = config->GetSurfFlowCoeff_FileName();
330  ofstream SurfFlow_file;
331 
332  /*--- Write file name with extension if unsteady ---*/
333  strcpy (cstr, filename.c_str());
334  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == TIME_SPECTRAL) {
335  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 10) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
336  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 10) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
337  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 100) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
338  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 1000) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
339  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
340 
341  } else if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() && config->GetWrt_Unsteady()) {
342  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 0) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 10)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
343  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 10) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
344  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 100) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
345  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 1000) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
346  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
347  }
348  else
349  SPRINTF (buffer, ".csv");

351  strcat (cstr, buffer);
352  SurfFlow_file.precision(15);
353  SurfFlow_file.open(cstr, ios::out);
354 
355  SurfFlow_file << "\"Global_Index\", \"x_coord\", \"y_coord\", ";
356  if (nDim == 3) SurfFlow_file << "\"z_coord\", ";
357  SurfFlow_file << "\"Pressure\", \"Pressure_Coefficient\", ";
358 
359  switch (solver) {
360  case EULER : SurfFlow_file << "\"Mach_Number\"" << "\n"; break;
361  case NAVIER_STOKES: case RANS:
362  if (nDim == 2) SurfFlow_file << "\"Skin_Friction_Coefficient_X\", \"Skin_Friction_Coefficient_Y\"" << "\n";
363  if (nDim == 3) SurfFlow_file << "\"Skin_Friction_Coefficient_X\", \"Skin_Friction_Coefficient_Y\", \"Skin_Friction_Coefficient_Z\"" << "\n";
364  break;
365  }
366 
367  /*--- Loop through all of the collected data and write each node's values ---*/
368 
369  unsigned long Total_Index;
370  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < nProcessor; iProcessor++) {
371  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < Buffer_Recv_nVertex[iProcessor]; iVertex++) {
372 
373  /*--- Current index position and global index ---*/
374  Total_Index = iProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface+iVertex;
375  Global_Index = Buffer_Recv_GlobalIndex[Total_Index];
376 
377  /*--- Retrieve the merged data for this node ---*/
378  xCoord = Buffer_Recv_Coord_x[Total_Index];
379  yCoord = Buffer_Recv_Coord_y[Total_Index];
380  if (nDim == 3) zCoord = Buffer_Recv_Coord_z[Total_Index];
381  Pressure = Buffer_Recv_Press[Total_Index];
382  PressCoeff = Buffer_Recv_CPress[Total_Index];
383 
384  /*--- Write the first part of the data ---*/
385  SurfFlow_file << scientific << Global_Index << ", " << xCoord << ", " << yCoord << ", ";
386  if (nDim == 3) SurfFlow_file << scientific << zCoord << ", ";
387  SurfFlow_file << scientific << Pressure << ", " << PressCoeff << ", ";
388 
389  /*--- Write the solver-dependent part of the data ---*/
390  switch (solver) {
391  case EULER :
392  Mach = Buffer_Recv_Mach[Total_Index];
393  SurfFlow_file << scientific << Mach << "\n";
394  break;
395  case NAVIER_STOKES: case RANS:
396  SkinFrictionCoeff[0] = Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_x[Total_Index];
397  SkinFrictionCoeff[1] = Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_y[Total_Index];
398  if (nDim == 3) SkinFrictionCoeff[2] = Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_z[Total_Index];
399  if (nDim == 2) SurfFlow_file << scientific << SkinFrictionCoeff[0] << ", " << SkinFrictionCoeff[1] << "\n";
400  if (nDim == 3) SurfFlow_file << scientific << SkinFrictionCoeff[0] << ", " << SkinFrictionCoeff[1] << ", " << SkinFrictionCoeff[2] << "\n";
401  break;
402  }
403  }
404  }
405 
406  /*--- Close the CSV file ---*/
407  SurfFlow_file.close();
408 
409  /*--- Release the recv buffers on the master node ---*/
410 
411  delete [] Buffer_Recv_Coord_x;
412  delete [] Buffer_Recv_Coord_y;
413  if (nDim == 3) delete [] Buffer_Recv_Coord_z;
414  delete [] Buffer_Recv_Press;
415  delete [] Buffer_Recv_CPress;
416  delete [] Buffer_Recv_Mach;
417  delete [] Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_x;
418  delete [] Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_y;
419  if (nDim == 3) delete [] Buffer_Recv_SkinFriction_z;
420  delete [] Buffer_Recv_HeatTransfer;
421  delete [] Buffer_Recv_GlobalIndex;
422 
423  delete [] Buffer_Recv_nVertex;
424 
425  }
426 
427  /*--- Release the memory for the remaining buffers and exit ---*/
428 
429  delete [] Buffer_Send_Coord_x;
430  delete [] Buffer_Send_Coord_y;
431  delete [] Buffer_Send_Coord_z;
432  delete [] Buffer_Send_Press;
433  delete [] Buffer_Send_CPress;
434  delete [] Buffer_Send_Mach;
435  delete [] Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_x;
436  delete [] Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_y;
437  delete [] Buffer_Send_SkinFriction_z;

439  delete [] Buffer_Send_GlobalIndex;

441 #endif

445 void COutput::SetSurfaceCSV_Adjoint(CConfig *config, CGeometry *geometry, CSolver *AdjSolver, CSolver *FlowSolution, unsigned long iExtIter, unsigned short val_iZone) {
446 
447 #ifndef HAVE_MPI
448 
449  unsigned long iPoint, iVertex, Global_Index;
450  su2double *Solution, xCoord, yCoord, zCoord;
451  unsigned short iMarker;
452  char cstr[200], buffer[50];
453  ofstream SurfAdj_file;
454 
455  /*--- Write file name with extension if unsteady ---*/
456  strcpy (cstr, config->GetSurfAdjCoeff_FileName().c_str());
457 
458  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == TIME_SPECTRAL) {
459  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 10) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
460  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 10) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
461  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 100) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
462  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 1000) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
463  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
464 
465  } else if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() && config->GetWrt_Unsteady()) {
466  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 0) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 10)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
467  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 10) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
468  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 100) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
469  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 1000) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
470  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
471  }
472  else
473  SPRINTF (buffer, ".csv");
474 
475  strcat(cstr, buffer);
476  SurfAdj_file.precision(15);
477  SurfAdj_file.open(cstr, ios::out);
478 
479  if (geometry->GetnDim() == 2) {
480  SurfAdj_file << "\"Point\",\"Sensitivity\",\"PsiRho\",\"Phi_x\",\"Phi_y\",\"PsiE\",\"x_coord\",\"y_coord\"";
481  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
482  SurfAdj_file << ",\"x_Sens\",\"y_Sens\"";
483  }
484  SurfAdj_file << "\n";
485 
486  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
487  if (config->GetMarker_All_Plotting(iMarker) == YES)
488  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
489  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
490  Global_Index = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
491  Solution = AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSolution();
492  xCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(0);
493  yCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(1);
494 
495  /*--- If US system, the output should be in inches ---*/
496 
497  if (config->GetSystemMeasurements() == US) {
498  xCoord *= 12.0;
499  yCoord *= 12.0;
500  }
501 
502  SurfAdj_file << scientific << Global_Index << ", " << AdjSolver->GetCSensitivity(iMarker, iVertex) << ", " << Solution[0] << ", "
503  << Solution[1] << ", " << Solution[2] << ", " << Solution[3] <<", " << xCoord <<", "<< yCoord;
504  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
505  SurfAdj_file << ", " << AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSensitivity(0) << ", " << AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSensitivity(1);
506  }
507  SurfAdj_file << "\n";
508  }
509  }
510  }
511 
512  if (geometry->GetnDim() == 3) {
513  SurfAdj_file << "\"Point\",\"Sensitivity\",\"PsiRho\",\"Phi_x\",\"Phi_y\",\"Phi_z\",\"PsiE\",\"x_coord\",\"y_coord\",\"z_coord\"";
514  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
515  SurfAdj_file << ",\"x_Sens\",\"y_Sens\",\"z_Sens\"";
516  }
517  SurfAdj_file << "\n";
518  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
519  if (config->GetMarker_All_Plotting(iMarker) == YES)
520  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
521  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
522  Global_Index = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
523  Solution = AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSolution();
524 
525  xCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(0);
526  yCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(1);
527  zCoord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(2);
528 
529  /*--- If US system, the output should be in inches ---*/
530 
531  if (config->GetSystemMeasurements() == US) {
532  xCoord *= 12.0;
533  yCoord *= 12.0;
534  zCoord *= 12.0;
535  }
536 
537  SurfAdj_file << scientific << Global_Index << ", " << AdjSolver->GetCSensitivity(iMarker, iVertex) << ", " << Solution[0] << ", "
538  << Solution[1] << ", " << Solution[2] << ", " << Solution[3] << ", " << Solution[4] << ", "<< xCoord <<", "<< yCoord <<", "<< zCoord;
539  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
540  SurfAdj_file << ", " << AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSensitivity(0) << ", " << AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSensitivity(1)
541  << ", " << AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSensitivity(2);
542  }
543  SurfAdj_file << "\n";
544  }
545  }
546  }
547 
548  SurfAdj_file.close();
549 
550 #else
551  int rank, iProcessor, nProcessor;
552 
553  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
554  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &nProcessor);
555 
556  unsigned short nDim = geometry->GetnDim(), iMarker;
557  su2double *Solution, *Coord;
558  unsigned long Buffer_Send_nVertex[1], iVertex, iPoint, nVertex_Surface = 0, nLocalVertex_Surface = 0,
559  MaxLocalVertex_Surface = 0, nBuffer_Scalar;
560  unsigned long *Buffer_Receive_nVertex = NULL;
561  ofstream SurfAdj_file;
562 
563  /*--- Write the surface .csv file ---*/
564  nLocalVertex_Surface = 0;
565  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++)
566  if (config->GetMarker_All_Plotting(iMarker) == YES)
567  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->GetnVertex(iMarker); iVertex++) {
568  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
569  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) nLocalVertex_Surface ++;
570  }
571 
572  if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
573  Buffer_Receive_nVertex = new unsigned long [nProcessor];
574 
575  Buffer_Send_nVertex[0] = nLocalVertex_Surface;
576 
577  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nLocalVertex_Surface, &MaxLocalVertex_Surface, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_MAX, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
578  SU2_MPI::Gather(&Buffer_Send_nVertex, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Receive_nVertex, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
579 
580  su2double *Buffer_Send_Coord_x = new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
581  su2double *Buffer_Send_Coord_y= new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
582  su2double *Buffer_Send_Coord_z= new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
583  unsigned long *Buffer_Send_GlobalPoint= new unsigned long[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
584  su2double *Buffer_Send_Sensitivity= new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
585  su2double *Buffer_Send_PsiRho= new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
586  su2double *Buffer_Send_Phi_x= new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
587  su2double *Buffer_Send_Phi_y= new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
588  su2double *Buffer_Send_Phi_z= new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
589  su2double *Buffer_Send_PsiE= new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
590 
591  su2double *Buffer_Send_Sens_x = NULL, *Buffer_Send_Sens_y = NULL, *Buffer_Send_Sens_z = NULL;
592 
593  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
594  Buffer_Send_Sens_x = new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
595  Buffer_Send_Sens_y = new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
596  if (nDim == 3){
597  Buffer_Send_Sens_z = new su2double[MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
598  }
599  }
600 
601  nVertex_Surface = 0;
602  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++)
603  if (config->GetMarker_All_Plotting(iMarker) == YES)
604  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->GetnVertex(iMarker); iVertex++) {
605  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
606  if (geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain()) {
607  Solution = AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSolution();
608  //Normal = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal();
609  Coord = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord();
610  //d = AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetForceProj_Vector();
611  Buffer_Send_GlobalPoint[nVertex_Surface] = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
612  Buffer_Send_Coord_x[nVertex_Surface] = Coord[0];
613  Buffer_Send_Coord_y[nVertex_Surface] = Coord[1];
614  Buffer_Send_Sensitivity[nVertex_Surface] = AdjSolver->GetCSensitivity(iMarker, iVertex);
615  Buffer_Send_PsiRho[nVertex_Surface] = Solution[0];
616  Buffer_Send_Phi_x[nVertex_Surface] = Solution[1];
617  Buffer_Send_Phi_y[nVertex_Surface] = Solution[2];
618  if (nDim == 2) Buffer_Send_PsiE[nVertex_Surface] = Solution[3];
619  if (nDim == 3) {
620  Buffer_Send_Coord_z[nVertex_Surface] = Coord[2];
621  Buffer_Send_Phi_z[nVertex_Surface] = Solution[3];
622  Buffer_Send_PsiE[nVertex_Surface] = Solution[4];
623  }
624  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
625  Buffer_Send_Sens_x[nVertex_Surface] = AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSensitivity(0);
626  Buffer_Send_Sens_y[nVertex_Surface] = AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSensitivity(1);
627  if (nDim == 3){
628  Buffer_Send_Sens_z[nVertex_Surface] = AdjSolver->node[iPoint]->GetSensitivity(2);
629  }
630  }
631 
632  /*--- If US system, the output should be in inches ---*/
633 
634  if (config->GetSystemMeasurements() == US) {
635  Buffer_Send_Coord_x[nVertex_Surface] *= 12.0;
636  Buffer_Send_Coord_y[nVertex_Surface] *= 12.0;
637  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Send_Coord_z[nVertex_Surface] *= 12.0;
638  }
639 
640  nVertex_Surface++;
641  }
642  }
643 
644  su2double *Buffer_Receive_Coord_x = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_Coord_y = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_Coord_z = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_Sensitivity = NULL,
645  *Buffer_Receive_PsiRho = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_Phi_x = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_Phi_y = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_Phi_z = NULL,
646  *Buffer_Receive_PsiE = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_Sens_x = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_Sens_y = NULL, *Buffer_Receive_Sens_z = NULL;
647  unsigned long *Buffer_Receive_GlobalPoint = NULL;
648 
649  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
650  Buffer_Receive_Coord_x = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
651  Buffer_Receive_Coord_y = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
652  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Receive_Coord_z = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
653  Buffer_Receive_GlobalPoint = new unsigned long [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
654  Buffer_Receive_Sensitivity = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
655  Buffer_Receive_PsiRho = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
656  Buffer_Receive_Phi_x = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
657  Buffer_Receive_Phi_y = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
658  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Receive_Phi_z = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
659  Buffer_Receive_PsiE = new su2double [nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
660  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
661  Buffer_Receive_Sens_x = new su2double[nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
662  Buffer_Receive_Sens_y = new su2double[nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
663  if (nDim == 3){
664  Buffer_Receive_Sens_z = new su2double[nProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface];
665  }
666  }
667  }
668 
669  nBuffer_Scalar = MaxLocalVertex_Surface;
670 
671  /*--- Send the information to the Master node ---*/
672  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Coord_x, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Coord_x, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
673  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Coord_y, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Coord_y, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
674  if (nDim == 3) SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Coord_z, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Coord_z, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
675  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_GlobalPoint, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Receive_GlobalPoint, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
676  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Sensitivity, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Sensitivity, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
677  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_PsiRho, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_PsiRho, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
678  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Phi_x, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Phi_x, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
679  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Phi_y, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Phi_y, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
680  if (nDim == 3) SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Phi_z, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Phi_z, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
681  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_PsiE, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_PsiE, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
682  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
683  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Sens_x, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Sens_x, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
684  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Sens_y, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Sens_y, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
685  if (nDim == 3){
686  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Sens_z, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Receive_Sens_z, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
687  }
688  }
689 
690  /*--- The master node is the one who writes the surface files ---*/
691  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
692  unsigned long iVertex, GlobalPoint, position;
693  char cstr[200], buffer[50];
694  ofstream SurfAdj_file;
695  string filename = config->GetSurfAdjCoeff_FileName();
696 
697  /*--- Write file name with extension if unsteady ---*/
698  strcpy (cstr, filename.c_str());
699 
700  if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() == TIME_SPECTRAL) {
701  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 10) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
702  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 10) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
703  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 100) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
704  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 1000) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
705  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone) >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
706 
707  } else if (config->GetUnsteady_Simulation() && config->GetWrt_Unsteady()) {
708  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 0) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 10)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
709  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 10) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
710  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 100) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
711  if ((SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 1000) && (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
712  if (SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter) >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.csv", SU2_TYPE::Int(iExtIter));
713  }
714  else
715  SPRINTF (buffer, ".csv");
716 
717  strcat (cstr, buffer);
718  SurfAdj_file.open(cstr, ios::out);
719  SurfAdj_file.precision(15);
720 
721  /*--- Write the 2D surface flow coefficient file ---*/
722  if (geometry->GetnDim() == 2) {
723 
724  SurfAdj_file << "\"Point\",\"Sensitivity\",\"PsiRho\",\"Phi_x\",\"Phi_y\",\"PsiE\",\"x_coord\",\"y_coord\"";
725  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
726  SurfAdj_file << ",\" x_Sens\",\"y_Sens\"";
727  }
728  SurfAdj_file << "\n";
729 
730  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < nProcessor; iProcessor++)
731  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < Buffer_Receive_nVertex[iProcessor]; iVertex++) {
732 
733  position = iProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface+iVertex;
734  GlobalPoint = Buffer_Receive_GlobalPoint[position];
735 
736  SurfAdj_file << scientific << GlobalPoint <<
737  ", " << Buffer_Receive_Sensitivity[position] << ", " << Buffer_Receive_PsiRho[position] <<
738  ", " << Buffer_Receive_Phi_x[position] << ", " << Buffer_Receive_Phi_y[position] <<
739  ", " << Buffer_Receive_PsiE[position] << ", " << Buffer_Receive_Coord_x[position] <<
740  ", "<< Buffer_Receive_Coord_y[position];
741  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
742  SurfAdj_file << ", " << Buffer_Receive_Sens_x[position] << ", " << Buffer_Receive_Sens_y[position];
743  }
744  SurfAdj_file << "\n";
745  }
746  }
747 
748  /*--- Write the 3D surface flow coefficient file ---*/
749  if (geometry->GetnDim() == 3) {
750 
751  SurfAdj_file << "\"Point\",\"Sensitivity\",\"PsiRho\",\"Phi_x\",\"Phi_y\",\"Phi_z\",\"PsiE\",\"x_coord\",\"y_coord\",\"z_coord\"";
752  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
753  SurfAdj_file << ",\"x_Sens\",\"y_Sens\",\"z_Sens\"";
754  }
755  SurfAdj_file << "\n";
756 
757  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < nProcessor; iProcessor++)
758  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < Buffer_Receive_nVertex[iProcessor]; iVertex++) {
759  position = iProcessor*MaxLocalVertex_Surface+iVertex;
760  GlobalPoint = Buffer_Receive_GlobalPoint[position];
761 
762  SurfAdj_file << scientific << GlobalPoint <<
763  ", " << Buffer_Receive_Sensitivity[position] << ", " << Buffer_Receive_PsiRho[position] <<
764  ", " << Buffer_Receive_Phi_x[position] << ", " << Buffer_Receive_Phi_y[position] << ", " << Buffer_Receive_Phi_z[position] <<
765  ", " << Buffer_Receive_PsiE[position] <<", "<< Buffer_Receive_Coord_x[position] <<
766  ", "<< Buffer_Receive_Coord_y[position] <<", "<< Buffer_Receive_Coord_z[position];
767  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
768  SurfAdj_file << ", " << Buffer_Receive_Sens_x[position] << ", " << Buffer_Receive_Sens_y[position] << ", " << Buffer_Receive_Sens_z[position];
769  }
770  SurfAdj_file << "\n";
771  }
772  }
773 
774  }
775 
776  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
777  delete [] Buffer_Receive_nVertex;
778  delete [] Buffer_Receive_Coord_x;
779  delete [] Buffer_Receive_Coord_y;
780  if (nDim == 3) delete [] Buffer_Receive_Coord_z;
781  delete [] Buffer_Receive_Sensitivity;
782  delete [] Buffer_Receive_PsiRho;
783  delete [] Buffer_Receive_Phi_x;
784  delete [] Buffer_Receive_Phi_y;
785  if (nDim == 3) delete [] Buffer_Receive_Phi_z;
786  delete [] Buffer_Receive_PsiE;
787  delete [] Buffer_Receive_GlobalPoint;
788  if (config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint()){
789  delete [] Buffer_Receive_Sens_x;
790  delete [] Buffer_Receive_Sens_y;
791  if (nDim == 3){
792  delete [] Buffer_Receive_Sens_z;
793  }
794  }
795  }
796 
797  delete [] Buffer_Send_Coord_x;
798  delete [] Buffer_Send_Coord_y;
799  delete [] Buffer_Send_Coord_z;
800  delete [] Buffer_Send_GlobalPoint;
801  delete [] Buffer_Send_Sensitivity;
802  delete [] Buffer_Send_PsiRho;
803  delete [] Buffer_Send_Phi_x;
804  delete [] Buffer_Send_Phi_y;
805  delete [] Buffer_Send_Phi_z;
806  delete [] Buffer_Send_PsiE;
807  if (Buffer_Send_Sens_x != NULL) delete [] Buffer_Send_Sens_x;
808  if (Buffer_Send_Sens_y != NULL) delete [] Buffer_Send_Sens_y;
809  if (Buffer_Send_Sens_z != NULL) delete [] Buffer_Send_Sens_z;
810 
811  SurfAdj_file.close();
812 
813 #endif
814 }
815 
816 void COutput::MergeConnectivity(CConfig *config, CGeometry *geometry, unsigned short val_iZone) {
817 
818  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
819  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
820 
821 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
822  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
823  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &size);
824 #endif
825 
826  /*--- Flags identifying the types of files to be written. ---*/
827 
828  bool Wrt_Vol = config->GetWrt_Vol_Sol();
829  bool Wrt_Srf = config->GetWrt_Srf_Sol();
830 
831  /*--- Merge connectivity for each type of element (excluding halos). Note
832  that we only need to merge the connectivity once, as it does not change
833  during computation. Check whether the base file has been written. ---*/
834 
835  /*--- Merge volumetric grid. ---*/
836 
837  if (Wrt_Vol) {
838 
839  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size != SINGLE_NODE) && (nGlobal_Tria != 0))
840  cout <<"Merging volumetric triangle grid connectivity." << endl;
841  MergeVolumetricConnectivity(config, geometry, TRIANGLE );
842 
843  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size != SINGLE_NODE) && (nGlobal_Quad != 0))
844  cout <<"Merging volumetric quadrilateral grid connectivity." << endl;
845  MergeVolumetricConnectivity(config, geometry, QUADRILATERAL );
846 
847  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size != SINGLE_NODE) && (nGlobal_Tetr != 0))
848  cout <<"Merging volumetric tetrahedron grid connectivity." << endl;
849  MergeVolumetricConnectivity(config, geometry, TETRAHEDRON );
850 
851  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size != SINGLE_NODE) && (nGlobal_Hexa != 0))
852  cout <<"Merging volumetric hexahedron grid connectivity." << endl;
853  MergeVolumetricConnectivity(config, geometry, HEXAHEDRON );
854 
855  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size != SINGLE_NODE) && (nGlobal_Pris != 0))
856  cout <<"Merging volumetric prism grid connectivity." << endl;
857  MergeVolumetricConnectivity(config, geometry, PRISM );
858 
859  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size != SINGLE_NODE) && (nGlobal_Pyra != 0))
860  cout <<"Merging volumetric pyramid grid connectivity." << endl;
861  MergeVolumetricConnectivity(config, geometry, PYRAMID );
862 
863  }
864 
865  /*--- Merge surface grid. ---*/
866 
867  if (Wrt_Srf) {
868 
869  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size != SINGLE_NODE) && (nGlobal_Line != 0))
870  cout <<"Merging surface line grid connectivity." << endl;
871  MergeSurfaceConnectivity(config, geometry, LINE);
872 
873  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size != SINGLE_NODE) && (nGlobal_BoundTria != 0))
874  cout <<"Merging surface triangle grid connectivity." << endl;
875  MergeSurfaceConnectivity(config, geometry, TRIANGLE);
876 
877  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (size != SINGLE_NODE) && (nGlobal_BoundQuad != 0))
878  cout <<"Merging surface quadrilateral grid connectivity." << endl;
879  MergeSurfaceConnectivity(config, geometry, QUADRILATERAL);
880 
881  }
882 
883  /*--- Update total number of volume elements after merge. ---*/
884 
885  nGlobal_Elem = nGlobal_Tria + nGlobal_Quad + nGlobal_Tetr +
886  nGlobal_Hexa + nGlobal_Pyra + nGlobal_Pris;
887 
888  /*--- Update total number of surface elements after merge. ---*/
889 
890  nSurf_Elem = nGlobal_Line + nGlobal_BoundTria + nGlobal_BoundQuad;
891 
892 }
893 
894 void COutput::MergeCoordinates(CConfig *config, CGeometry *geometry) {
895 
896  /*--- Local variables needed on all processors ---*/
897 
898  unsigned short iDim, nDim = geometry->GetnDim();
899  unsigned long iPoint;
900 
901  unsigned short kind_SU2 = config->GetKind_SU2();
902 
903 #ifndef HAVE_MPI
904 
905  /*--- In serial, the single process has access to all geometry, so simply
906  load the coordinates into the data structure. ---*/
907 
908  unsigned short iMarker;
909  unsigned long iVertex, nTotalPoints = 0;
910  int SendRecv;
911 
912  bool isPeriodic;
913 
914  /*--- First, create a structure to locate any periodic halo nodes ---*/
915  int *Local_Halo = new int[geometry->GetnPoint()];
916  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry->GetnPoint(); iPoint++)
917  Local_Halo[iPoint] = !geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain();
918 
919  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
920  if (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == SEND_RECEIVE) {
921  SendRecv = config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(iMarker);
922  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
923  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
924 
925  /* --- For SU2_CFD and SU2_SOL we want to remove the periodic halo nodes,
926  * but for SU2_DEF we want them to be included, therefore the definition of a periodic point
927  * is different in each case --- */
928 
929  if (kind_SU2 == SU2_DEF){
930  isPeriodic = ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() > 0));
931  }else{
932  isPeriodic = ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() > 0) &&
933  (geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() % 2 == 1));
934  }
935 
936  if (isPeriodic && (SendRecv < 0)) {
937  Local_Halo[iPoint] = false;
938  }
939  }
940 
941  }
942  }
943 
944  /*--- Total number of points in the mesh (this might include periodic points). ---*/
945  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry->GetnPoint(); iPoint++)
946  if (!Local_Halo[iPoint]) nTotalPoints++;
947 
948  nGlobal_Poin = nTotalPoints;
949  nGlobal_Doma = geometry->GetnPointDomain();
950 
951  /*--- Allocate the coordinates data structure. ---*/
952 
953  Coords = new su2double*[nDim];
954  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
955  Coords[iDim] = new su2double[nGlobal_Poin];
956  }
957 
958  /*--- Loop over the mesh to collect the coords of the local points ---*/
959 
960  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry->GetnPoint(); iPoint++) {
961 
962  /*--- Check if the node belongs to the domain (i.e, not a halo node).
963  Sort by the global index, even in serial there is a renumbering (e.g. RCM). ---*/
964 
965  if (!Local_Halo[iPoint]) {
966 
967  /*--- Retrieve the current coordinates at this node. ---*/
968 
969  unsigned long iGlobal_Index = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
970 
971  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
972  Coords[iDim][iGlobal_Index] = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord(iDim);
973 
974  /*--- If US system, the output should be in inches ---*/
975 
976  if ((config->GetSystemMeasurements() == US) && (config->GetKind_SU2() != SU2_DEF)) {
977  Coords[iDim][iGlobal_Index] *= 12.0;
978  }
979 
980  }
981 
982  }
983  }
984 
985 
986  delete [] Local_Halo;
987 
988 #else
989 
990  /*--- MPI preprocessing ---*/
991  int iProcessor, nProcessor, rank;
992  unsigned long jPoint;
993 
994  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
995  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &nProcessor);
996 
997  bool Wrt_Halo = config->GetWrt_Halo(), isPeriodic;
998 
999  /*--- Local variables needed for merging the geometry with MPI. ---*/
1000 
1001  unsigned long iVertex, iMarker;
1002  unsigned long Buffer_Send_nPoin[1], *Buffer_Recv_nPoin = NULL;
1003  unsigned long nLocalPoint = 0, MaxLocalPoint = 0;
1004  unsigned long iGlobal_Index = 0, nBuffer_Scalar = 0;
1005 
1006  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) Buffer_Recv_nPoin = new unsigned long[nProcessor];
1007 
1008  int *Local_Halo = new int[geometry->GetnPoint()];
1009  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry->GetnPoint(); iPoint++)
1010  Local_Halo[iPoint] = !geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain();
1011 
1012  /*--- Search all send/recv boundaries on this partition for any periodic
1013  nodes that were part of the original domain. We want to recover these
1014  for visualization purposes. ---*/
1015 
1016  if (Wrt_Halo) {
1017  nLocalPoint = geometry->GetnPoint();
1018  } else {
1019  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
1020  if (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == SEND_RECEIVE) {
1021 
1022  /*--- Checking for less than or equal to the rank, because there may
1023  be some periodic halo nodes that send info to the same rank. ---*/
1024 
1025  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
1026  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
1027 
1028  /* --- For SU2_CFD and SU2_SOL we want to remove the periodic halo nodes,
1029  * but for SU2_DEF we want them to be included, therefore the definition of a periodic point
1030  * is different in each case --- */
1031 
1032  if (kind_SU2 == SU2_DEF){
1033  isPeriodic = ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() > 0));
1034  }else{
1035  isPeriodic = ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() > 0) &&
1036  (geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() % 2 == 1));
1037  }
1038  if (isPeriodic){
1039  Local_Halo[iPoint] = false;
1040  }
1041  }
1042  }
1043  }
1044 
1045  /*--- Sum total number of nodes that belong to the domain ---*/
1046 
1047  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry->GetnPoint(); iPoint++)
1048  if (Local_Halo[iPoint] == false)
1049  nLocalPoint++;
1050  }
1051  Buffer_Send_nPoin[0] = nLocalPoint;
1052 
1053  /*--- Communicate the total number of nodes on this domain. ---*/
1054 
1055  SU2_MPI::Gather(&Buffer_Send_nPoin, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG,
1056  Buffer_Recv_nPoin, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1057  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nLocalPoint, &MaxLocalPoint, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_MAX, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1058 
1059  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1060  nGlobal_Doma = 0;
1061  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < nProcessor; iProcessor++) {
1062  nGlobal_Doma += Buffer_Recv_nPoin[iProcessor];
1063  }
1064  }
1065  nBuffer_Scalar = MaxLocalPoint;
1066 
1067  /*--- Send and Recv buffers. ---*/
1068 
1069  su2double *Buffer_Send_X = new su2double[MaxLocalPoint];
1070  su2double *Buffer_Recv_X = NULL;
1071 
1072  su2double *Buffer_Send_Y = new su2double[MaxLocalPoint];
1073  su2double *Buffer_Recv_Y = NULL;
1074 
1075  su2double *Buffer_Send_Z = NULL, *Buffer_Recv_Z = NULL;
1076  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Send_Z = new su2double[MaxLocalPoint];
1077 
1078  unsigned long *Buffer_Send_GlobalIndex = new unsigned long[MaxLocalPoint];
1079  unsigned long *Buffer_Recv_GlobalIndex = NULL;
1080 
1081  /*--- Prepare the receive buffers in the master node only. ---*/
1082 
1083  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1084 
1085  Buffer_Recv_X = new su2double[nProcessor*MaxLocalPoint];
1086  Buffer_Recv_Y = new su2double[nProcessor*MaxLocalPoint];
1087  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Recv_Z = new su2double[nProcessor*MaxLocalPoint];
1088  Buffer_Recv_GlobalIndex = new unsigned long[nProcessor*MaxLocalPoint];
1089 
1090  /*--- Sum total number of nodes to be written and allocate arrays ---*/
1091  nGlobal_Poin = 0;
1092  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < nProcessor; iProcessor++) {
1093  nGlobal_Poin += Buffer_Recv_nPoin[iProcessor];
1094  }
1095  Coords = new su2double*[nDim];
1096  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
1097  Coords[iDim] = new su2double[nGlobal_Poin];
1098  }
1099  }
1100 
1101  /*--- Main communication routine. Loop over each coordinate and perform
1102  the MPI comm. Temporary 1-D buffers are used to send the coordinates at
1103  all nodes on each partition to the master node. These are then unpacked
1104  by the master and sorted by global index in one large n-dim. array. ---*/
1105 
1106  /*--- Loop over this partition to collect the coords of the local points. ---*/
1107  su2double *Coords_Local; jPoint = 0;
1108  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry->GetnPoint(); iPoint++) {
1109 
1110  /*--- Check for halos and write only if requested ---*/
1111  if (!Local_Halo[iPoint] || Wrt_Halo) {
1112 
1113  /*--- Retrieve local coordinates at this node. ---*/
1114  Coords_Local = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetCoord();
1115 
1116  /*--- Load local coords into the temporary send buffer. ---*/
1117  Buffer_Send_X[jPoint] = Coords_Local[0];
1118  Buffer_Send_Y[jPoint] = Coords_Local[1];
1119  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Send_Z[jPoint] = Coords_Local[2];
1120 
1121  /*--- If US system, the output should be in inches ---*/
1122 
1123  if ((config->GetSystemMeasurements() == US) && (config->GetKind_SU2() != SU2_DEF)) {
1124  Buffer_Send_X[jPoint] *= 12.0;
1125  Buffer_Send_Y[jPoint] *= 12.0;
1126  if (nDim == 3) Buffer_Send_Z[jPoint] *= 12.0;
1127  }
1128 
1129  /*--- Store the global index for this local node. ---*/
1130  Buffer_Send_GlobalIndex[jPoint] = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
1131 
1132  /*--- Increment jPoint as the counter. We need this because iPoint
1133  may include halo nodes that we skip over during this loop. ---*/
1134  jPoint++;
1135  }
1136  }
1137 
1138  /*--- Gather the coordinate data on the master node using MPI. ---*/
1139 
1140  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_X, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_X, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1141  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Y, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_Y, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1142  if (nDim == 3) {
1143  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Z, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, Buffer_Recv_Z, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1144  }
1145  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_GlobalIndex, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Recv_GlobalIndex, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1146 
1147  /*--- The master node unpacks and sorts this variable by global index ---*/
1148 
1149  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1150  jPoint = 0;
1151  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < nProcessor; iProcessor++) {
1152  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < Buffer_Recv_nPoin[iProcessor]; iPoint++) {
1153  /*--- Get global index, then loop over each variable and store ---*/
1154  iGlobal_Index = Buffer_Recv_GlobalIndex[jPoint];
1155  if (iGlobal_Index >= nGlobal_Poin){
1156  cout << iGlobal_Index << " " << nGlobal_Poin << endl;
1157  }
1158  Coords[0][iGlobal_Index] = Buffer_Recv_X[jPoint];
1159  Coords[1][iGlobal_Index] = Buffer_Recv_Y[jPoint];
1160  if (nDim == 3) Coords[2][iGlobal_Index] = Buffer_Recv_Z[jPoint];
1161  jPoint++;
1162  }
1163  /*--- Adjust jPoint to index of next proc's data in the buffers. ---*/
1164  jPoint = (iProcessor+1)*nBuffer_Scalar;
1165  }
1166  }
1167 
1168  /*--- Immediately release the temporary data buffers. ---*/
1169 
1170  delete [] Local_Halo;
1171  delete [] Buffer_Send_X;
1172  delete [] Buffer_Send_Y;
1173  if (Buffer_Send_Z != NULL) delete [] Buffer_Send_Z;
1174  delete [] Buffer_Send_GlobalIndex;
1175  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1176  delete [] Buffer_Recv_X;
1177  delete [] Buffer_Recv_Y;
1178  if (Buffer_Recv_Z != NULL) delete [] Buffer_Recv_Z;
1179  delete [] Buffer_Recv_GlobalIndex;
1180  delete [] Buffer_Recv_nPoin;
1181  }
1182 
1183 #endif
1184 
1185 }
1186 
1187 void COutput::MergeVolumetricConnectivity(CConfig *config, CGeometry *geometry, unsigned short Elem_Type) {
1188 
1189  int iProcessor;
1190  unsigned short NODES_PER_ELEMENT;
1191  unsigned long iPoint, iNode, jNode;
1192  unsigned long iElem = 0;
1193  unsigned long nLocalElem = 0, nElem_Total = 0;
1194 
1195  unsigned long iVertex, iMarker;
1196  unsigned long jElem;
1197  int SendRecv, RecvFrom;
1198 
1199  unsigned long Buffer_Send_nElem[1], *Buffer_Recv_nElem = NULL;
1200  unsigned long nBuffer_Scalar = 0;
1201  unsigned long kNode = 0, kElem = 0;
1202  unsigned long MaxLocalElem = 0, iGlobal_Index, jPoint, kPoint;
1203 
1204  bool Wrt_Halo = config->GetWrt_Halo();
1205  bool *Write_Elem = NULL, notPeriodic, notHalo, addedPeriodic, isPeriodic;
1206 
1207  unsigned short kind_SU2 = config->GetKind_SU2();
1208 
1209  int *Conn_Elem = NULL;
1210 
1211  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
1212  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
1213 
1214 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1215  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
1216  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &size);
1217 #endif
1218 
1219 
1220  /*--- Store the local number of this element type and the number of nodes
1221  per this element type. In serial, this will be the total number of this
1222  element type in the entire mesh. In parallel, it is the number on only
1223  the current partition. ---*/
1224 
1225  switch (Elem_Type) {
1226  case TRIANGLE:
1227  nLocalElem = geometry->GetnElemTria();
1228  NODES_PER_ELEMENT = N_POINTS_TRIANGLE;
1229  break;
1230  case QUADRILATERAL:
1231  nLocalElem = geometry->GetnElemQuad();
1232  NODES_PER_ELEMENT = N_POINTS_QUADRILATERAL;
1233  break;
1234  case TETRAHEDRON:
1235  nLocalElem = geometry->GetnElemTetr();
1236  NODES_PER_ELEMENT = N_POINTS_TETRAHEDRON;
1237  break;
1238  case HEXAHEDRON:
1239  nLocalElem = geometry->GetnElemHexa();
1240  NODES_PER_ELEMENT = N_POINTS_HEXAHEDRON;
1241  break;
1242  case PRISM:
1243  nLocalElem = geometry->GetnElemPris();
1244  NODES_PER_ELEMENT = N_POINTS_PRISM;
1245  break;
1246  case PYRAMID:
1247  nLocalElem = geometry->GetnElemPyra();
1248  NODES_PER_ELEMENT = N_POINTS_PYRAMID;
1249  break;
1250  default:
1251  cout << "Error: Unrecognized element type \n";
1252  exit(EXIT_FAILURE); break;
1253  }
1254 
1255  /*--- Find the max number of this element type among all
1256  partitions and set up buffers. ---*/
1257 
1258  Buffer_Send_nElem[0] = nLocalElem;
1259  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) Buffer_Recv_nElem = new unsigned long[size];
1260 
1261 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1262  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nLocalElem, &MaxLocalElem, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_MAX, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1263  SU2_MPI::Gather(&Buffer_Send_nElem, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Recv_nElem, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1264 #else
1265  MaxLocalElem = nLocalElem;
1266  Buffer_Recv_nElem[0] = Buffer_Send_nElem[0];
1267 #endif
1268 
1269  nBuffer_Scalar = MaxLocalElem*NODES_PER_ELEMENT;
1270 
1271  /*--- Send and Recv buffers ---*/
1272 
1273  unsigned long *Buffer_Send_Elem = new unsigned long[nBuffer_Scalar];
1274  unsigned long *Buffer_Recv_Elem = NULL;
1275 
1276  unsigned short *Buffer_Send_Halo = new unsigned short[MaxLocalElem];
1277  unsigned short *Buffer_Recv_Halo = NULL;
1278 
1279  /*--- Prepare the receive buffers on the master node only. ---*/
1280 
1281  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1282  Buffer_Recv_Elem = new unsigned long[size*nBuffer_Scalar];
1283  Buffer_Recv_Halo = new unsigned short[size*MaxLocalElem];
1284  Conn_Elem = new int[size*MaxLocalElem*NODES_PER_ELEMENT];
1285  }
1286 
1287  /*--- Force the removal of all added periodic elements (use global index).
1288  First, we isolate and create a list of all added periodic points, excluding
1289  those that we part of the original domain (we want these to be in the
1290  output files). ---*/
1291 
1292  vector<unsigned long> Added_Periodic;
1293  Added_Periodic.clear();
1294 
1295  if (kind_SU2 != SU2_DEF){
1296  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
1297  if (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == SEND_RECEIVE) {
1298  SendRecv = config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(iMarker);
1299  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
1300  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
1301 
1302  if ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() > 0) &&
1303  (geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() % 2 == 0) &&
1304  (SendRecv < 0)) {
1305  Added_Periodic.push_back(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex());
1306  }
1307  }
1308  }
1309  }
1310  }
1311 
1312  /*--- Now we communicate this information to all processors, so that they
1313  can force the removal of these particular nodes by flagging them as halo
1314  points. In general, this should be a small percentage of the total mesh,
1315  so the communication/storage costs here shouldn't be prohibitive. ---*/
1316 
1317  /*--- First communicate the number of points that each rank has found ---*/
1318  unsigned long nAddedPeriodic = 0, maxAddedPeriodic = 0;
1319  unsigned long Buffer_Send_nAddedPeriodic[1], *Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic = NULL;
1320  Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic = new unsigned long[size];
1321 
1322  nAddedPeriodic = Added_Periodic.size();
1323  Buffer_Send_nAddedPeriodic[0] = nAddedPeriodic;
1324 
1325 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1326  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nAddedPeriodic, &maxAddedPeriodic, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG,
1327  MPI_MAX, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1328  SU2_MPI::Allgather(&Buffer_Send_nAddedPeriodic, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG,
1329  Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1330 #else
1331  maxAddedPeriodic = nAddedPeriodic;
1332  Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic[0] = Buffer_Send_nAddedPeriodic[0];
1333 #endif
1334 
1335  /*--- Communicate the global index values of all added periodic nodes. ---*/
1336  unsigned long *Buffer_Send_AddedPeriodic = new unsigned long[maxAddedPeriodic];
1337  unsigned long *Buffer_Recv_AddedPeriodic = new unsigned long[size*maxAddedPeriodic];
1338 
1339  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < Added_Periodic.size(); iPoint++) {
1340  Buffer_Send_AddedPeriodic[iPoint] = Added_Periodic[iPoint];
1341  }
1342 
1343  /*--- Gather the element connectivity information. All processors will now
1344  have a copy of the global index values for all added periodic points. ---*/
1345 
1346 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1347  SU2_MPI::Allgather(Buffer_Send_AddedPeriodic, maxAddedPeriodic, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG,
1348  Buffer_Recv_AddedPeriodic, maxAddedPeriodic, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG,
1349  MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1350 #else
1351  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < maxAddedPeriodic; iPoint++) Buffer_Recv_AddedPeriodic[iPoint] = Buffer_Send_AddedPeriodic[iPoint];
1352 #endif
1353 
1354  /*--- Search all send/recv boundaries on this partition for halo cells. In
1355  particular, consider only the recv conditions (these are the true halo
1356  nodes). Check the ranks of the processors that are communicating and
1357  choose to keep only the halo cells from the higher rank processor. Here,
1358  we are also choosing to keep periodic nodes that were part of the original
1359  domain. We will check the communicated list of added periodic points. ---*/
1360 
1361  int *Local_Halo = new int[geometry->GetnPoint()];
1362  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry->GetnPoint(); iPoint++)
1363  Local_Halo[iPoint] = !geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain();
1364 
1365  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
1366  if (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == SEND_RECEIVE) {
1367  SendRecv = config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(iMarker);
1368  RecvFrom = abs(SendRecv)-1;
1369 
1370  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
1371  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
1372  iGlobal_Index = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
1373 
1374  /*--- We need to keep one copy of overlapping halo cells. ---*/
1375  notHalo = ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() == 0) &&
1376  (SendRecv < 0) && (rank > RecvFrom));
1377 
1378  /*--- We want to keep the periodic nodes that were part of the original domain.
1379  * For SU2_DEF we want to keep all periodic nodes. ---*/
1380 
1381  if (kind_SU2 == SU2_DEF){
1382  isPeriodic = ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() > 0));
1383  }else{
1384  isPeriodic = ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() > 0) &&
1385  (geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() % 2 == 1));
1386  }
1387 
1388  notPeriodic = (isPeriodic && (SendRecv < 0));
1389 
1390  /*--- Lastly, check that this isn't an added periodic point that
1391  we will forcibly remove. Use the communicated list of these points. ---*/
1392  addedPeriodic = false; kPoint = 0;
1393  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < size; iProcessor++) {
1394  for (jPoint = 0; jPoint < Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic[iProcessor]; jPoint++) {
1395  if (iGlobal_Index == Buffer_Recv_AddedPeriodic[kPoint+jPoint])
1396  addedPeriodic = true;
1397  }
1398  /*--- Adjust jNode to index of next proc's data in the buffers. ---*/
1399  kPoint = (iProcessor+1)*maxAddedPeriodic;
1400  }
1401 
1402  /*--- If we found either of these types of nodes, flag them to be kept. ---*/
1403  if ((notHalo || notPeriodic) && !addedPeriodic) {
1404  Local_Halo[iPoint] = false;
1405  }
1406  }
1407  }
1408  }
1409 
1410  /*--- Loop over all elements in this partition and load the
1411  elements of the current type into the buffer to be sent to
1412  the master node. ---*/
1413 
1414  jNode = 0; jElem = 0;
1415  for (iElem = 0; iElem < geometry->GetnElem(); iElem++) {
1416  if (geometry->elem[iElem]->GetVTK_Type() == Elem_Type) {
1417 
1418  /*--- Loop over all nodes in this element and load the
1419  connectivity into the send buffer. ---*/
1420 
1421  Buffer_Send_Halo[jElem] = false;
1422  for (iNode = 0; iNode < NODES_PER_ELEMENT; iNode++) {
1423 
1424  /*--- Store the global index values directly. ---*/
1425 
1426  iPoint = geometry->elem[iElem]->GetNode(iNode);
1427  Buffer_Send_Elem[jNode] = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
1428 
1429  /*--- Check if this is a halo node. If so, flag this element
1430  as a halo cell. We will use this later to sort and remove
1431  any duplicates from the connectivity list. ---*/
1432 
1433  if (Local_Halo[iPoint]) {
1434  Buffer_Send_Halo[jElem] = true;
1435  }
1436 
1437  /*--- Increment jNode as the counter. We need this because iElem
1438  may include other elements that we skip over during this loop. ---*/
1439 
1440  jNode++;
1441  }
1442  jElem++;
1443  }
1444  }
1445 
1446  /*--- Gather the element connectivity information. ---*/
1447 
1448 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1449  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Elem, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Recv_Elem, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1450  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Halo, MaxLocalElem, MPI_UNSIGNED_SHORT, Buffer_Recv_Halo, MaxLocalElem, MPI_UNSIGNED_SHORT, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1451 #else
1452  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nBuffer_Scalar; iPoint++) Buffer_Recv_Elem[iPoint] = Buffer_Send_Elem[iPoint];
1453  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < MaxLocalElem; iPoint++) Buffer_Recv_Halo[iPoint] = Buffer_Send_Halo[iPoint];
1454 #endif
1455 
1456  /*--- The master node unpacks and sorts the connectivity. ---*/
1457 
1458  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1459 
1460  /*--- We need to remove any duplicate elements (halo cells) that
1461  exist on multiple partitions. Start by initializing all elements
1462  to the "write" state by using a boolean array. ---*/
1463 
1464  Write_Elem = new bool[size*MaxLocalElem];
1465  for (iElem = 0; iElem < size*MaxLocalElem; iElem++) {
1466  Write_Elem[iElem] = true;
1467  }
1468 
1469  /*--- Remove the rind layer from the solution only if requested ---*/
1470 
1471  if (!Wrt_Halo) {
1472 
1473  /*--- Loop for flagging duplicate elements so that they are not
1474  included in the final connectivity list. ---*/
1475 
1476  kElem = 0;
1477  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < size; iProcessor++) {
1478  for (iElem = 0; iElem < Buffer_Recv_nElem[iProcessor]; iElem++) {
1479 
1480  /*--- Check if this element was marked as a halo. ---*/
1481  if (Buffer_Recv_Halo[kElem+iElem])
1482  Write_Elem[kElem+iElem] = false;
1483 
1484  }
1485  kElem = (iProcessor+1)*MaxLocalElem;
1486  }
1487  }
1488 
1489  /*--- Store the unique connectivity list for this element type. ---*/
1490 
1491  jNode = 0; kNode = 0; jElem = 0; nElem_Total = 0;
1492  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < size; iProcessor++) {
1493  for (iElem = 0; iElem < Buffer_Recv_nElem[iProcessor]; iElem++) {
1494 
1495  /*--- Only write the elements that were flagged for it. ---*/
1496  if (Write_Elem[jElem+iElem]) {
1497 
1498  /*--- Increment total count for this element type ---*/
1499  nElem_Total++;
1500 
1501  /*--- Get global index, then loop over each variable and store.
1502  Note that we are adding one to the index value because CGNS/Tecplot
1503  use 1-based indexing.---*/
1504 
1505  for (iNode = 0; iNode < NODES_PER_ELEMENT; iNode++) {
1506  Conn_Elem[kNode] = (int)Buffer_Recv_Elem[jNode+iElem*NODES_PER_ELEMENT+iNode] + 1;
1507  kNode++;
1508  }
1509  }
1510  }
1511  /*--- Adjust jNode to index of next proc's data in the buffers. ---*/
1512  jElem = (iProcessor+1)*MaxLocalElem;
1513  jNode = (iProcessor+1)*nBuffer_Scalar;
1514  }
1515  }
1516 
1517  /*--- Immediately release the temporary buffers. ---*/
1518  delete [] Buffer_Send_Elem;
1519  delete [] Buffer_Send_Halo;
1520  delete [] Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic;
1521  delete [] Buffer_Send_AddedPeriodic;
1522  delete [] Buffer_Recv_AddedPeriodic;
1523  delete [] Local_Halo;
1524  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1525  delete [] Buffer_Recv_nElem;
1526  delete [] Buffer_Recv_Elem;
1527  delete [] Buffer_Recv_Halo;
1528  delete [] Write_Elem;
1529  }
1530 
1531  /*--- Store the particular global element count in the class data,
1532  and set the class data pointer to the connectivity array. ---*/
1533 
1534  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1535  switch (Elem_Type) {
1536  case TRIANGLE:
1537  nGlobal_Tria = nElem_Total;
1538  if (nGlobal_Tria > 0) Conn_Tria = Conn_Elem;
1539  break;
1540  case QUADRILATERAL:
1541  nGlobal_Quad = nElem_Total;
1542  if (nGlobal_Quad > 0) Conn_Quad = Conn_Elem;
1543  break;
1544  case TETRAHEDRON:
1545  nGlobal_Tetr = nElem_Total;
1546  if (nGlobal_Tetr > 0) Conn_Tetr = Conn_Elem;
1547  break;
1548  case HEXAHEDRON:
1549  nGlobal_Hexa = nElem_Total;
1550  if (nGlobal_Hexa > 0) Conn_Hexa = Conn_Elem;
1551  break;
1552  case PRISM:
1553  nGlobal_Pris = nElem_Total;
1554  if (nGlobal_Pris > 0) Conn_Pris = Conn_Elem;
1555  break;
1556  case PYRAMID:
1557  nGlobal_Pyra = nElem_Total;
1558  if (nGlobal_Pyra > 0) Conn_Pyra = Conn_Elem;
1559  break;
1560  default:
1561  cout << "Error: Unrecognized element type \n";
1562  exit(EXIT_FAILURE); break;
1563  }
1564  }
1565 
1566 }
1567 
1568 void COutput::MergeSurfaceConnectivity(CConfig *config, CGeometry *geometry, unsigned short Elem_Type) {
1569 
1570  unsigned short NODES_PER_ELEMENT;
1571 
1572  unsigned short iMarker;
1573  unsigned long iPoint, iNode, jNode;
1574  unsigned long iElem = 0;
1575  unsigned long nLocalElem = 0, nElem_Total = 0;
1576 
1577  int iProcessor;
1578  unsigned long jElem;
1579 
1580  unsigned long iVertex;
1581 
1582  int SendRecv, RecvFrom;
1583 
1584  unsigned long Buffer_Send_nElem[1], *Buffer_Recv_nElem = NULL;
1585  unsigned long nBuffer_Scalar = 0;
1586  unsigned long kNode = 0, kElem = 0;
1587  unsigned long MaxLocalElem = 0, iGlobal_Index, jPoint, kPoint;
1588 
1589  bool Wrt_Halo = config->GetWrt_Halo();
1590  bool *Write_Elem = NULL, notPeriodic, notHalo, addedPeriodic;
1591 
1592 
1593  int *Conn_Elem = NULL;
1594 
1595  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
1596  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
1597 
1598 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1599  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
1600  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &size);
1601 #endif
1602 
1603  /*--- Store the local number of this element type and the number of nodes
1604  per this element type. In serial, this will be the total number of this
1605  element type in the entire mesh. In parallel, it is the number on only
1606  the current partition. ---*/
1607 
1608  nLocalElem = 0;
1609 
1610  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
1611  if (config->GetMarker_All_Plotting(iMarker) == YES) {
1612  for (iElem = 0; iElem < geometry->GetnElem_Bound(iMarker); iElem++) {
1613  if (geometry->bound[iMarker][iElem]->GetVTK_Type() == Elem_Type) {
1614  nLocalElem++;
1615  }
1616  }
1617  }
1618  }
1619 
1620  switch (Elem_Type) {
1621  case LINE:
1622  NODES_PER_ELEMENT = N_POINTS_LINE;
1623  break;
1624  case TRIANGLE:
1625  NODES_PER_ELEMENT = N_POINTS_TRIANGLE;
1626  break;
1627  case QUADRILATERAL:
1628  NODES_PER_ELEMENT = N_POINTS_QUADRILATERAL;
1629  break;
1630  default:
1631  cout << "Error: Unrecognized element type \n";
1632  exit(EXIT_FAILURE); break;
1633  }
1634 
1635  /*--- Find the max number of this element type among all
1636  partitions and set up buffers. ---*/
1637 
1638  Buffer_Send_nElem[0] = nLocalElem;
1639  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) Buffer_Recv_nElem = new unsigned long[size];
1640 
1641 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1642  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nLocalElem, &MaxLocalElem, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_MAX, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1643  SU2_MPI::Gather(&Buffer_Send_nElem, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Recv_nElem, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1644 #else
1645  MaxLocalElem = nLocalElem;
1646  Buffer_Recv_nElem[0] = Buffer_Send_nElem[0];
1647 #endif
1648 
1649  nBuffer_Scalar = MaxLocalElem*NODES_PER_ELEMENT;
1650 
1651  /*--- Send and Recv buffers ---*/
1652 
1653  unsigned long *Buffer_Send_Elem = new unsigned long[nBuffer_Scalar];
1654  unsigned long *Buffer_Recv_Elem = NULL;
1655 
1656  unsigned short *Buffer_Send_Halo = new unsigned short[MaxLocalElem];
1657  unsigned short *Buffer_Recv_Halo = NULL;
1658 
1659  /*--- Prepare the receive buffers on the master node only. ---*/
1660 
1661  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1662  Buffer_Recv_Elem = new unsigned long[size*nBuffer_Scalar];
1663  Buffer_Recv_Halo = new unsigned short[size*MaxLocalElem];
1664  Conn_Elem = new int[size*MaxLocalElem*NODES_PER_ELEMENT];
1665  }
1666 
1667  /*--- Force the removal of all added periodic elements (use global index).
1668  First, we isolate and create a list of all added periodic points, excluding
1669  those that we part of the original domain (we want these to be in the
1670  output files). ---*/
1671 
1672  vector<unsigned long> Added_Periodic;
1673  Added_Periodic.clear();
1674  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
1675  if (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == SEND_RECEIVE) {
1676  SendRecv = config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(iMarker);
1677  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
1678  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
1679  if ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() > 0) &&
1680  (geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() % 2 == 0) &&
1681  (SendRecv < 0)) {
1682  Added_Periodic.push_back(geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex());
1683  }
1684  }
1685  }
1686  }
1687 
1688  /*--- Now we communicate this information to all processors, so that they
1689  can force the removal of these particular nodes by flagging them as halo
1690  points. In general, this should be a small percentage of the total mesh,
1691  so the communication/storage costs here shouldn't be prohibitive. ---*/
1692 
1693  /*--- First communicate the number of points that each rank has found ---*/
1694  unsigned long nAddedPeriodic = 0, maxAddedPeriodic = 0;
1695  unsigned long Buffer_Send_nAddedPeriodic[1], *Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic = NULL;
1696  Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic = new unsigned long[size];
1697 
1698  nAddedPeriodic = Added_Periodic.size();
1699  Buffer_Send_nAddedPeriodic[0] = nAddedPeriodic;
1700 
1701 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1702  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&nAddedPeriodic, &maxAddedPeriodic, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG,
1703  MPI_MAX, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1704  SU2_MPI::Allgather(&Buffer_Send_nAddedPeriodic, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG,
1705  Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic, 1, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1706 #else
1707  maxAddedPeriodic = nAddedPeriodic;
1708  Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic[0] = Buffer_Send_nAddedPeriodic[0];
1709 #endif
1710 
1711  /*--- Communicate the global index values of all added periodic nodes. ---*/
1712  unsigned long *Buffer_Send_AddedPeriodic = new unsigned long[maxAddedPeriodic];
1713  unsigned long *Buffer_Recv_AddedPeriodic = new unsigned long[size*maxAddedPeriodic];
1714 
1715  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < Added_Periodic.size(); iPoint++) {
1716  Buffer_Send_AddedPeriodic[iPoint] = Added_Periodic[iPoint];
1717  }
1718 
1719  /*--- Gather the element connectivity information. All processors will now
1720  have a copy of the global index values for all added periodic points. ---*/
1721 
1722 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1723  SU2_MPI::Allgather(Buffer_Send_AddedPeriodic, maxAddedPeriodic, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG,
1724  Buffer_Recv_AddedPeriodic, maxAddedPeriodic, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG,
1725  MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1726 #else
1727  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < maxAddedPeriodic; iPoint++) Buffer_Recv_AddedPeriodic[iPoint] = Buffer_Send_AddedPeriodic[iPoint];
1728 #endif
1729 
1730  /*--- Search all send/recv boundaries on this partition for halo cells. In
1731  particular, consider only the recv conditions (these are the true halo
1732  nodes). Check the ranks of the processors that are communicating and
1733  choose to keep only the halo cells from the higher rank processor. Here,
1734  we are also choosing to keep periodic nodes that were part of the original
1735  domain. We will check the communicated list of added periodic points. ---*/
1736 
1737  int *Local_Halo = new int[geometry->GetnPoint()];
1738  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < geometry->GetnPoint(); iPoint++)
1739  Local_Halo[iPoint] = !geometry->node[iPoint]->GetDomain();
1740 
1741  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++) {
1742  if (config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker) == SEND_RECEIVE) {
1743  SendRecv = config->GetMarker_All_SendRecv(iMarker);
1744  RecvFrom = abs(SendRecv)-1;
1745 
1746  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
1747  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
1748  iGlobal_Index = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
1749 
1750  /*--- We need to keep one copy of overlapping halo cells. ---*/
1751  notHalo = ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() == 0) &&
1752  (SendRecv < 0) && (rank > RecvFrom));
1753 
1754  /*--- We want to keep the periodic nodes that were part of the original domain ---*/
1755  notPeriodic = ((geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() > 0) &&
1756  (geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetRotation_Type() % 2 == 1) &&
1757  (SendRecv < 0));
1758 
1759  /*--- Lastly, check that this isn't an added periodic point that
1760  we will forcibly remove. Use the communicated list of these points. ---*/
1761  addedPeriodic = false; kPoint = 0;
1762  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < size; iProcessor++) {
1763  for (jPoint = 0; jPoint < Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic[iProcessor]; jPoint++) {
1764  if (iGlobal_Index == Buffer_Recv_AddedPeriodic[kPoint+jPoint])
1765  addedPeriodic = true;
1766  }
1767  /*--- Adjust jNode to index of next proc's data in the buffers. ---*/
1768  kPoint = (iProcessor+1)*maxAddedPeriodic;
1769  }
1770 
1771  /*--- If we found either of these types of nodes, flag them to be kept. ---*/
1772  if ((notHalo || notPeriodic) && !addedPeriodic) {
1773  Local_Halo[iPoint] = false;
1774  }
1775  }
1776  }
1777  }
1778 
1779  /*--- Loop over all elements in this partition and load the
1780  elements of the current type into the buffer to be sent to
1781  the master node. ---*/
1782  jNode = 0; jElem = 0;
1783  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); iMarker++)
1784  if (config->GetMarker_All_Plotting(iMarker) == YES)
1785  for (iElem = 0; iElem < geometry->GetnElem_Bound(iMarker); iElem++) {
1786 
1787  if (geometry->bound[iMarker][iElem]->GetVTK_Type() == Elem_Type) {
1788 
1789  /*--- Loop over all nodes in this element and load the
1790  connectivity into the send buffer. ---*/
1791 
1792  Buffer_Send_Halo[jElem] = false;
1793  for (iNode = 0; iNode < NODES_PER_ELEMENT; iNode++) {
1794 
1795  /*--- Store the global index values directly. ---*/
1796 
1797  iPoint = geometry->bound[iMarker][iElem]->GetNode(iNode);
1798  Buffer_Send_Elem[jNode] = geometry->node[iPoint]->GetGlobalIndex();
1799 
1800  /*--- Check if this is a halo node. If so, flag this element
1801  as a halo cell. We will use this later to sort and remove
1802  any duplicates from the connectivity list. ---*/
1803 
1804  if (Local_Halo[iPoint])
1805  Buffer_Send_Halo[jElem] = true;
1806 
1807  /*--- Increment jNode as the counter. We need this because iElem
1808  may include other elements that we skip over during this loop. ---*/
1809 
1810  jNode++;
1811  }
1812  jElem++;
1813  }
1814  }
1815 
1816  /*--- Gather the element connectivity information. ---*/
1817 
1818 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1819  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Elem, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, Buffer_Recv_Elem, nBuffer_Scalar, MPI_UNSIGNED_LONG, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1820  SU2_MPI::Gather(Buffer_Send_Halo, MaxLocalElem, MPI_UNSIGNED_SHORT, Buffer_Recv_Halo, MaxLocalElem, MPI_UNSIGNED_SHORT, MASTER_NODE, MPI_COMM_WORLD);
1821 #else
1822  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < nBuffer_Scalar; iPoint++) Buffer_Recv_Elem[iPoint] = Buffer_Send_Elem[iPoint];
1823  for (iPoint = 0; iPoint < MaxLocalElem; iPoint++) Buffer_Recv_Halo[iPoint] = Buffer_Send_Halo[iPoint];
1824 #endif
1825 
1826  /*--- The master node unpacks and sorts the connectivity. ---*/
1827 
1828  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1829 
1830  /*--- We need to remove any duplicate elements (halo cells) that
1831  exist on multiple partitions. Start by initializing all elements
1832  to the "write" state by using a boolean array. ---*/
1833 
1834  Write_Elem = new bool[size*MaxLocalElem];
1835  for (iElem = 0; iElem < size*MaxLocalElem; iElem++) {
1836  Write_Elem[iElem] = true;
1837  }
1838 
1839  /*--- Remove the rind layer from the solution only if requested ---*/
1840 
1841  if (!Wrt_Halo) {
1842 
1843  /*--- Loop for flagging duplicate elements so that they are not
1844  included in the final connectivity list. ---*/
1845 
1846  kElem = 0;
1847  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < size; iProcessor++) {
1848  for (iElem = 0; iElem < Buffer_Recv_nElem[iProcessor]; iElem++) {
1849 
1850  /*--- Check if this element was marked as a halo. ---*/
1851  if (Buffer_Recv_Halo[kElem+iElem])
1852  Write_Elem[kElem+iElem] = false;
1853 
1854  }
1855  kElem = (iProcessor+1)*MaxLocalElem;
1856  }
1857  }
1858 
1859  /*--- Store the unique connectivity list for this element type. ---*/
1860 
1861  jNode = 0; kNode = 0; jElem = 0; nElem_Total = 0;
1862  for (iProcessor = 0; iProcessor < size; iProcessor++) {
1863  for (iElem = 0; iElem < Buffer_Recv_nElem[iProcessor]; iElem++) {
1864 
1865  /*--- Only write the elements that were flagged for it. ---*/
1866  if (Write_Elem[jElem+iElem]) {
1867 
1868  /*--- Increment total count for this element type ---*/
1869  nElem_Total++;
1870 
1871  /*--- Get global index, then loop over each variable and store.
1872  Note that we are adding one to the index value because CGNS/Tecplot
1873  use 1-based indexing.---*/
1874 
1875  for (iNode = 0; iNode < NODES_PER_ELEMENT; iNode++) {
1876  Conn_Elem[kNode] = (int)Buffer_Recv_Elem[jNode+iElem*NODES_PER_ELEMENT+iNode] + 1;
1877  kNode++;
1878  }
1879  }
1880  }
1881  /*--- Adjust jNode to index of next proc's data in the buffers. ---*/
1882  jElem = (iProcessor+1)*MaxLocalElem;
1883  jNode = (iProcessor+1)*nBuffer_Scalar;
1884  }
1885  }
1886 
1887  /*--- Immediately release the temporary buffers. ---*/
1888  delete [] Buffer_Send_Elem;
1889  delete [] Buffer_Send_Halo;
1890  delete [] Buffer_Recv_nAddedPeriodic;
1891  delete [] Buffer_Send_AddedPeriodic;
1892  delete [] Buffer_Recv_AddedPeriodic;
1893  delete [] Local_Halo;
1894  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
1895  delete [] Buffer_Recv_nElem;
1896  delete [] Buffer_Recv_Elem;
1897  delete [] Buffer_Recv_Halo;
1898  delete [] Write_Elem;
1899  }
1900
